The paper deals with pedestrian motion prediction using machine learning techniques, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of semantic features and Gaussian Process also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluation of the approach on real-world data collected from a vehicle suggests a potential application in systems and control (cs.SY).
